title: For Sale/Trade:  Compete Mosin Nagant 91/30 sporterized package. Open to trade offers.
postcontent:
I have my complete deer hunting rifle package for sale or trade. It is a Mosin Nagant 91/30 that has been completely modernized. I bought it as an unfinished project from previous owner and finished it. It worked great for me for this past deer season. Only reason I'm selling is because I am thinking about getting something new to have some range fun with. 

This has an ati monte carlo camo stock, ati bent bolt kit, ati scope mount, improved one finger loop safety, barska 3-9x42 scope with lens focus adjustment and back lit red and green cross hairs. The barrel had been shortened to 24" by the previous owner and I re crowned the barrel with a full 79 degree target crown and polished the crown to eliminate any grooves or chatter marks. Camo stock had some chips from use, bolt has a hole on the front side of the handle from having it backwards while installing the bent handle. Nothing interferes with good operation. Only thing this rifle would need is the scope zeroed better. I ran out of time before deer hunting due to work schedule, but I didn't have a problem hitting an 8" circle from 100 yards repeatedly,  so that was good enough for me for this year.

This takes a classic and makes it like a modern hunting rifle. My favorite thing about this rifle is the ability to target shoot or stock up surplus ammo for about $0.17 a round. That's crazy cheap. I bought 3 boxes of premium soft point hunting rounds for $13.99 for a box of 20. That's cheap for a large round like this 7.62x54r. 

Included in this package is:

Rifle with scope

title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith & Wesson Shield .40 (Not effected by Shield recall)
postcontent:
One owner Shield in excellent condition.  150 rounds through it , after which is was cleaned/lubed and put away in its box.  I am a Vet who is anal about his firearms, as anyone can see who looks at them.  I also build custom handguns and rifles, so I am careful with them and treat them as they should be treated.  
This Shield functiones 100%, with Zero malfunctions of any kind ever with both the standard and extended magazine.  This Sheild was NOT effected by the recent recall having to do with the trigger return.  Never modified or messed with, 100% original.
VERY nice for daily carry with its slim profile, light weight and overall size, it just doesn't fit my hands, (too small for me) so I am not as accurate with it.  I've had other people pick it up and shoot the "10" ring to death with it, (making me look like a horrible shot).  
I've found another daily carry piece that fits my hands well and with this Shield being my only firearm in .40, it is just sitting in the safe.
I am looking to sell/trade it with everything it came with;  The original Box, both magazines, (one 6 round and one extended 7 round), gun lock, etc.  It will also come with 20 rounds of Hornady "critical defense" carry rounds, (my preferred carry ammo, if the buyer wants it) and a quality, (not cheap-o) black leather 3 slot belt holster.  These extras alone would run you almost $100, and the pistol was $425 for a total of about $525 new.  So, I think that my asking price is more than fair considering what you'd be getting and its overall condition.  I think it's a great deal vs. buying just a new Shield without the added stuff you're getting here.  
I will need a copy of your NH drivers license and carry permit for sale, or we can meet at an FFL of your choice to transfer, you cover the transfer fee.  I believe I may have another 50-100 rounds of Fiocchi ammo if the buyer is interested, and I would be happy to sell that at a discounted price.
Serious buyers or trade offers only PLEASE.  If you send me a trade offer, I will respond to it IF I AM INTERESTED!  If you don't hear back within 48 hours, I am not interested.  
Thanks for your time, I know this reads like a novel but I try to make my listings as clear as possible.  I have 100% feedback everywhere I have sold online including many firearm parts and complete rifles/handguns and I plan on keeping it that way.  Happy shooting!

title: For Sale:  eagle gun company
postcontent:
Eagle Gun Company Thompson style carbine. This is a rare weapon. It is an open bolt fired carbine. The Eagle Carbine was developed and manufactured in small numbers from 1964-68. The gun has iron sights (which were only used during the first year of production making this particular gun even harder to find than ones made during the next 3 years of production). As far as legality, This particular design was followed by the Spitfire, Commando and Apache Carbines which appeared in the early 1970's. The Spitfire's and Apache's were banned by the ATF and reclassified as "machine guns", in effect making this already rare Eagle Carbine the only legal version of this type of firearm.
